data.description: Ranch-style three bedroom, two and a half bathroom renovated house located close to US 123 and downtown Seneca. This house offers plenty of space for entertaining and an abundance of natural light for family and guests. Walk through the front door and into the foyer that opens into a large, inviting living room with restored hardwoods. The living room leads into a well appointed kitchen featuring custom woodworking, plenty of cabinetry, stainless steel appliances and large windows for an airy feel. Just off the kitchen area, you'll find a spacious family room featuring a half bath, beautiful built in books shelves and could be used as a possible fourth bedroom or second master. The master suite is located on main level features restored hardwood floors and an updated full bath with shower/tub combination. Additionally, there are two other guest bedrooms with one guest bedroom featuring a full bath. Storage is plentiful with a half basement/garage and even a wood burning stove. In addition, there is a staired attic for even more storage. Located between Hwy 123 and downtown Seneca, this house is situated in a lovely, quiet neighborhood offering both convenience and privacy. This is a MUST see!
